Bottomline Technologies, Inc. (NASDAQ:EPAY) Stock Traded 8.7% Above Its 50 Day Average - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Bottomline Technologies, Inc. (NASDAQ:EPAY) Stock Traded 8.7% Above Its 50 Day Average
July 21, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





It is currently trading at $28.50 marginally over the 50 day moving average which is $26.21 and which is just over the 200 day moving average of $25.05.  The 50 day moving average was up $2.29 whereas the 200 day moving average was up $3.45 or +13.77%.  Bottomline Technologies, Inc. shares had a trading volume of 256K on Friday.  Volume was down 6.10% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Bottomline Technologies, Inc. (NASDAQ:EPAY) has been the object of insider selling activity recently.   MD, Digital Banking Norman J. Deluca sold 2,750 shares at an average price of $25.33 on Thu the 15th. That brings Deluca’s holdings to $2,116,423 as reported to the SEC.
 These funds have also shifted positions in (EPAY).   As of quarter end Bb&t Corp had sold 184 shares trimming its holdings by 1.9%. The value of the investment in EPAY went from $232,000 to $247,000 increasing 6.5% quarter to quarter. As of the end of the quarter Roanoke Asset Management Corp/ Ny had disposed of  a total of 5,775 shares trimming its position 8.7%. The value of the total investment in Bottomline Technologies, Inc. decreased from $1,572,000 to $1,560,000 a change of $12,000 quarter over quarter.
 Aperio Group, LLC bolstered its stake by buying 1,447 shares an increase of 8.3% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Aperio Group, LLC now controls 18,863 shares valued at $485,000. The value of the position overall is up by 17.7%. As of the end of the quarter Nisa Investment Advisors, LLC had acquired  a total of 200 shares growing its stake by 47.6%. The value of the investment in (EPAY) went from $10,000 to $16,000 a change of 60.0% since the last quarter.





  RBC Capital began coverage of EPAY giving it an initial rating of “Sector Perform” and setting a price target of $26.00. August 26 investment analysts at Canaccord Genuity left the stock rating at “Hold” and moved down the price target from $28.00 to $25.00.
 On June 29, 2016 First Analysis starting coverage on EPAY with a rating of “Overweight”. On April 29 the stock rating was downgraded from “Outperform” to “Market Perform” in a report from William Blair.
 On April 29 the company was set at “Market Perform” according to a Raymond James report which was a cut from the previous “Outperform” rating. On October 30 the company was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” by analysts at Craig-Hallum.
 The company is trading down by -0.56 percent from yesterday’s close.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $-0.88 and is estimated to be $0.96 for the current year with 38,134,000 shares presently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is expected be $0.24 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $1.06. 
 Bottomline Technologies (de), Inc., launched on August 12, 1997, is involved in providing a set of cloud-based business payment, digital banking, fraud prevention, payment and financial document solutions. The Company helps businesses pay and get paid. The Company offers hosted or Software as a Service (SaaS) solutions, as well as software designed to run on-site at the customer’s location. The Company operates through four segments: Payments and Transactional Documents, Hosted Solutions, Digital Banking and Other. Its products and services are sold to customers operating in many different industries throughout the world, but principally in the United States, the United Kingdom and continental Europe regions..






